                                <h2>Youth Mentorship program</h2>
                                <p>Every year the Conestoga Robotics Youth Mentorship program assembles a team comprised of club members willing to help with teaching the youth about robotics. The goal is to spark an interest in the young minds to pursue robotics in their future.</p>
                                <p>To achieve this goal, the youth mentors travel down to middle schools and other youth organizations such as girl scouts, and they present robotics to the aspiring engineers in such a way that is easy for them to understand. The end result of this is that it inspires and builds a passion in the youth for solving real-world problems through automation and robotics.</p>
